  "text": "The particle characterization for radiation and sedimentation was very simple in CCM3 and CAM2. Sedimentation of cloud particles was ignored. Ice particle optical radii were a function only of pressure. Those models assumed the cloud ice radius to be 10 m below 800 mb and 30 m above 400 mb with linear variation in pressure between those levels. Recent measurement and modeling studies (see Mitchell et al. 1996a,b) suggest that ice particle sizes are better characterized according to temperature. In CAM3, we have assumed that ice particle sizes are a function only of temperature, following [CITATION_1] , as shown in Fig. 5 .",
